  "mitigations": [
    {
      "id": "M1026",
      "name": "Privileged Account Management",
      "description": "Limit permissions so that users and user groups cannot create tokens. This setting should be defined for the local system account only. GPO: Computer Configuration > [Policies] > Windows Settings > Security Settings > Local Policies > User Rights Assignment: Create a token object. Also define who can create a process level token to only the local and network service through GPO: Computer Configuration > [Policies] > Windows Settings > Security Settings > Local Policies > User Rights Assignment: Replace a process level token. Administrators should log in as a standard user but run their tools with administrator privileges using the built-in access token manipulation command runas.",
